ol.li:
Here is one: the fourth equation is redundant but still OK.

							\syseq{
							 x  +  y  -  z  +  w  =  0;
                						\. \+ y  -  z \+ \. =  0;
                						\. \+ \. \+ 2z  + 2w = 0;
               						\. \+ \. \+ z  +  w  =  0
							}

This is one.

							\syseq{
							x  +  y  -  z  +  w  =  0;
             						x  +  y  -  z  +  w  =  0;
             						x  +  y  -  z  +  w  =  0;
             						x  +  y  -  z  +  w  =  0 
							}

statement.p:
Solve this system. Then solve the associated homogeneous system.

				\syseq{
				 x  + y  - 2z = 0;
        				x  - y  \+ \. = -3;
        				3x - y  - 2z = -6;
           				\. \+  2y - 2z = 3  
				}

answer.p:
This reduction solves the system.


					\amat{
					1 1  -2 0;
         					1 -1 0  3;
         					3 -1  -2 -6;
         					0 2   -2 3
					}
					\quad\xrightarrow{}\quad
					&\amat{
					1 1  -2 0;
         					0 -2 2  -3;
         					0 -4  4  -6;
         					0 2   -2 3
					}


					\quad\xrightarrow{}\quad
					&\amat{
					1 1  -2 0;
         					0 -2  2  -3;
         					0 0  0  0;
         					0 0   0  0
					}


				The solution set is:
				\bigl\{\vec{-\frac{3}{2} \frac{3}{2} 0} + \vec{1 1 1}z \mid z \text{ in } \R \bigr\}
			Similarly we can reduce the associated homogeneous system


					\amat{
					1 1  -2 0;
         					1 -1  0  0;
         					3 -1  -2 0;
         					0 2   -2 0
					}
					\quad\xrightarrow{}\quad
					&\amat{
					 1 1   -2 0;
         					0  -2  2  0; 
         					0 -4  4  0;
         					0 2  -2 0
					}


					\quad\xrightarrow{}\quad
					&\amat{
					1 1  -2 0;
        	 				0 -2  2  0;
         					0 0  0  0;
         					0 0   0  0
					}


				to get its solution set:
				\bigl\{\vec{1 1 1}z \mid z \text{ in } \R \bigr\}
